<br>
I applaud Verant's attempt, but it is another factor where the game and roleplaying do not mix, and it is another example how 'realism' in the game is selective.  As you have pointed out with /tell... where were we ever given a roleplaying background to justify tells?  Or bind points?  Or dying and respawning at our bind point naked?  How is it that we don't die when we run out of food and water... we just get week?<br>
<br>
I've said it before, but this 'selective' realism just doesn't work.  It was a great plan 2+ years ago, but we've learned a lot since then.  We've learned there are a lot of things that are not realistic (even for a fantasy setting), and those things that get put in for realism are simply annoying.<br>
<br>
I'm in line with the rest of the posts as well.  I also agree that Human is fine, although it seems there are bugs in the redesigned languages anyway.  The only thing I can suggest that seems out of line is half elves in Kelethin should default to elf instead of human, but I suppose that would require more coding than they wanted to do.  *shrugs*  It's no biggy (I just had to switch), just doesn't make sense. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueyasfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EyasFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/14/01 5:29:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RE:Since its Roleplaying prefered....</span><hr size=1> I don't think your points are well thought out.<br>
